Restore per-draw FIFO drains in aurora's GX immediate-mode and display-list paths.

Aurora commit 71d8462 ("Introduce render worker & revamp RmlUi backend")
commented out the per-draw fifo::drain() calls in GXEnd() and
GXCallDisplayList() with "TEMP: debugging aid" markers, intending to
defer FIFO processing into a buffered path. The texture-replacement
hash code (texture_replacement.cpp:compute_referenced_tlut_hash) still
reads s_loadedTluts[obj.tlut], which GXLoadTlut overwrites synchronously
on the game thread. With drains removed, FIFO commands accumulate while
the game blasts through subsequent GXLoadTlut calls, so by the time the
FIFO actually drains the s_loadedTluts slot has been overwritten and
find_replacement computes the wrong tlutHash for earlier queued draws,
missing user texture-pack entries.

Restoring the drains forces FIFO processing per-draw, keeping
s_loadedTluts consistent with the draw being processed. This is a
stop-gap revert of aurora's stop-gap until upstream lands a proper fix.

diff --git a/extern/aurora/lib/dolphin/gx/GXDispList.cpp b/extern/aurora/lib/dolphin/gx/GXDispList.cpp
--- a/extern/aurora/lib/dolphin/gx/GXDispList.cpp
+++ b/extern/aurora/lib/dolphin/gx/GXDispList.cpp
@@ -58,12 +58,8 @@ void GXCallDisplayList(const void* data, u32 nbytes) {
     __GXSendFlushPrim();
   }

-  // Write display list contents to the FIFO
-  aurora::gx::fifo::write_data(data, nbytes);
-
-  // TEMP: debugging aid
-  // aurora::gx::fifo::drain();
-  // aurora::gx::fifo::process(static_cast<const u8*>(data), nbytes, true);
+  aurora::gx::fifo::drain();
+  aurora::gx::fifo::process(static_cast<const u8*>(data), nbytes, true);
 }

